2. Structural Element Usage

The header contains the site title and navigation.

The nav element contains the main navigation links.

The main element contains the primary page content.

The article contains the main instructional content.

Each section groups related content by topic.

The aside contains related but secondary information about the W3C warning.

The footer contains contact and site information.


3. ARIA Roles

role="banner" is used on the header.

role="navigation" is used on the nav.

role="main" is used on the main element.

role="complementary" is used on the aside.

role="contentinfo" is used on the footer.
